
[1]mile

   MILE, n. [L. mille passus, a thousand paces; passus being dropped in
   common usage.] A measure of length or distance, containing eight
   furlongs, 320 rods, poles or perches, 1760 yards, 5280 feet, or 80
   chains. The Roman mile was a thousand paces, equal to 1600 yards
   English measure.
